            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="0"/>
                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>nus NI<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>rnus Teđđ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">Ta</supplied>citus <abbr>Pedu</abbr> MED<supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">Ia</supplied>nuarin</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> Atticus Max<lb break="no" n="4"/>iminus Dutti Sene<lb break="no" n="5"/>cianus Senecio Cupit<lb break="no" n="6"/>us Celsi <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olverunt</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibentes</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>aeti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ua</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ecunia</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>K</abbr><ex>alendis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Sep</abbr><ex>tembribus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Pris</abbr><ex>co</ex></expan> et <expan><abbr>Apo</abbr><ex>llinare</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Unterer Teil eines Altars mit Ansatz des Sockels. Z. 3: z.B. Pedu(llus). MED dürfte auch zu einem Namen gehören. Z. 5-7: nach Kakoschke eher entweder drei Söhne eines Celsus, also Senecianus (et) Senecio (et) Cupitus Celsi (filii), oder zwei Personen namens Senecianus Senecio und Cupitus Celsi (filius).</p>
            </div>
